    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-19T09:00:00-05:00" n="585"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A/3–1953: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 585<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Syria (<persName corresp="#p_MJS1"
                            type="from">Moose</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d585fn1">Repeated to Tel Aviv, Amman, Jerusalem, London, and
                        Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-19T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 19, 1953—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>601. According <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss>, meeting March 16 Syrian
                    and Israeli delegations discussed northern and central zones but not southern
                    zone since documentation on land ownership not submitted (<gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 592, March 12).<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d585fn2">Telegram 592 from Damascus contained a report of the
                        Syria-Israel meeting of Mar. 10. (683.84A/3–1253)</note> Israelis confirmed
                    willingness give up Dardara and land above Huleh necessary compensate
                    dispossessed central zone Arabs. <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> Chairman
                    puzzled by uncompromising attitude <pb facs="1195" n="1155" xml:id="pg_1155"/>
                    Syrians who presented new demands such as for unlimited irrigation rights from
                    upper Jordan waters. <persName corresp="#p_TCS1">Taxis</persName> endeavoring
                    obtain appointments see Shishikli ascertain whether Syrians changing position on
                    zone settlement and to urge constructive attitude. Date next <gloss
                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> meeting not yet fixed.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_TCS1">Taxis</persName> scheduled sail for US April 6.
                    Apparently not yet decided who will replace him on Syro-Israel <gloss
                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
